<br>
There is a mindset out there that a good anytime style would be too overpowering for Savages.  I'm curious, what's your opinion?<br>
<br>
From where I sit, only a level 14 Savage, it seems to me that there is a need to revisit this issue.  My thought is that it would not be overpowering to rework the the 29th style, Kelgor's Claw with the following:<br>
<br>
Prerequisite:  none (currently the case)<br>
<br>
Attack Bonus:  low (currently none)<br>
<br>
Defense Bonus:  none (currently the case)<br>
<br>
Fatigue Cost:  medium (currently the case)<br>
<br>
Damage Bonus:  low (currently none)<br>
<br>
Effect:  increased evade chance (currently the case)<br>
<br>
This does not, on the surface appear especially overpowering.  It would add a small damage bonus and a small to hit bonus.  If the damage bonus - because the chance to multi-hit truly does increase significantly - makes this overpowering, perhaps the low bonus to hit - at the very least - could be added.  What do you think? <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 4.4 Berserker<br>
Hammer Tyme - 50th RR 3.1 Skald<br>
Syf Stormcrow - 48th RR 3.4 Huntress</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#000000>(12/6/02 11:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anytime Style</span><hr size=1> I like this idea and I think it would really put a finishing touch on the style line (once we get the effects actually <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>working</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->).  I've pushed it forward to Mythic. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/trevanti/savagebanner5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=connorrowynsun>Connor Rowynsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#000000>(12/9/02 5:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anytime Style</span><hr size=1> Thanks Trev.<br>
<br>
I've got my Savage to level 23 now and am more convinced than ever that at a minimum, a to hit bonus is necessary.  On yellow con mobs, its not an issue, but on red and purple there are alot of misses if I&quot;m main tank because I have to use styles with no to hit bonuses.<br>
<br>
If I'm not main tank, but damage dealer - which is the preferable role for a Savage - its less of a problem because I can spam the rear positional attack (Clan's Call) which has a medium to hit bonus and make contact (and deal a short duration stun).  The style that plays off of it, Clan's Might, does nice damage, but because it has no to hit bonus, it often misses.<br>
<br>
It would be good to look at some of our styles and rework the to hit bonuses.  I would pay special attention to Kelgor's Claw, Taunting Call (if you have a high mob on you, it does not good to use a detaunt that you can't land -  no to hit bonus), and Clan's Might.  I would add a low damage bonus to Kelgor's Claw as well.<br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
<br>
