<br>
Since a lot of our damage is based off reactionary chains, I like the higher defensive bonus.<br>
<br>
At level 23, I've actually gotten a high of 7 Totemic Fear styles off in a row. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I evaded 3 times in a row, and after the speed debuff and hasting myself, I was hitting 3 times for every one swing of the mob.  I probably would have had 9, but the mob died on 7.  Hehe.<br>
<br>
<br>
Aggro is a funny thing.  Some aggro mobs you can sneak up behind without them being tipped off.  Ants in muspelheim, snow imps in the frontier, etc.  For anything I can get behind, combat generally goes:<br>
<br>
Clan's Call<br>
Clan's Might<br>
Haste Buff<br>
Evade Buff<br>
Speed Debuff<br>
Totemic Fear with Taunting Call as backup <br>
Repeat last step until mob is dead.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/trevanti/savagebanner5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hypatian>Hypatian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#000000>(12/23/02 6:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://laurelin.dementia.org:8080/users/jprevost/enay-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I agree</span><hr size=1> I use Tribal Rage backed by Totemic Fear and seem to get a good number of hits.  When attacking high purples in Trollheim, using no style at all resulted in pretty much zero hits.  But when I used Totemic Fear (and failed to perform it perfectly, obviously, because otherwise I'd have aggro and be in trouble), I hit reasonably often for a level 35 character attacking level 50+ mobs.<br>
<br>
I'm going to do more research on this, but I think that the rumour I heard on the IGN boards was true for once (that imprefectly performed styles still apply to-hit bonuses.)<br>
<br>
Even if this is true, I'd argue for the change you recommend to Kelgor's Claw.  Not because I think we need an anytime style, but because the medium endurance use (which is fairly high for hand-to-hand styles) for only &quot;+ evade&quot; is so unattractive that I haven't even considered using the style at all.  If it had the low attack + low damage bonus that you suggest, or even just a medium attack + no damage bonus, I'd start to think about rearranging my quickbars. <p>Harana Nyao - Guinevere - Valkyn Savage<br>
Lorride Olsdottir - Guinevere - Norse Huntress<br>
Alanis Salameh - Tristan - Saracen Paladin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#000000>(4/8/03 9:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I agree</span><hr size=1> These days in PvE I use Totemic Fear with Kelgor's Claw backing it up.  The bonus to Evade is substantial.<br>
<br>
In RvR, I almost exclusively use the side and rear stun styles.  I do use Totemic Fear sometimes tho, in the rare occassion that someone is actually tanking me.  Most people just run. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/trevanti/savagebanner5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=9.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.emailToFriend?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.threadControl?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notific